why choose git over the existing  version control systems

Limitations of existing version control systems
--> existing version control systems have centralized architecture this means there is a single central server that stores  all the  project files
--> Changes canot be done offline
user->retrieve files->make changes->commit
users can retrieve the files to the workspaces make neccessary changes and commit them to the central server
-->All changes made in central server
--> users must be connecting to the central server to make any neccessary changes and rectify the errors this means there is no room for error
these are the  major challenges existing  version control system it is difficult to work with this so git is the one stop solution 

WHAT IS GIT?
- GIT IS VERSION CONTROL SYSTEM
- IT IS A DISTRIBUTED VERSION CONTROL SYSTEM SUCH AS SPEED, DATA INTEGRITY, SECURITY
- GIT IS ORIGINALLY DEVELPED BY LINUSTORVAULDS  IN 2005 HE IS A CREATOR OF GIT
- GIT IS DESIGNED FOR OVERCOME THE LIMITATIONS TO  THE OTHER VERSION CONTROL SYSTEMS
